5. libras] The sense requires a smaller coin than the angel ; probably the French livre which was equi-valent to the florin current (cf. Ep. 436. 5n). In the exchange of the day 21 English: 3 angels = 7 or 8 florins current. For payments to Erasmus in livres see Epp. 179, 181 introdd.

6. etiam] In addition to the Brussels martyrs: for whom see Ep. 1384. 2n.

7. exustum] Jo. Valliere, an illiterate hermit of Falaise in Normandy, aged c. 40, was burnt at Paris, 8 Aug. 1523, for declaring that Christ was the son of Joseph and Mary: see Journal d'un bour-qeois de Par-is, ed. V. L. Bourrilly,
